<p>I am using jquery ui slider widget which slides in pixel value instead of percentage unit value.</p>  <p>i am using.</p>  <pre><code>$( "#Liveslider" ).slider({ value:0, min: 0, max: 100, step: 50, animate: true}); </code></pre>  <p>output in DOM is</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div id="Liveslider" class="ui-slider ui-slider-horizontal ui-widget ui-widget-content ui-corner-all"&gt; &lt;span class="ui-slider-handle ui-state-default ui-corner-all" tabindex="0" style="left: 50px; transition-property: all; transition-duration: 0s; transition-timing-function: cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1);"&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>above in span tag for handle creates inline styles  as </p>  <pre><code>style="left: 50px; transition-property: all; transition-duration: 0s; transition-timing-function: cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1);" </code></pre>  <p>left value of handle creates in 50px unit instead of 50% unit</p>  <p>how to solve this situation?</p>